Experiment 2 of 4

Matt Green

In this experiment we did not count any response as an error, instead we coded them as expected, borderline, and extreme.

These are the example instructions:
vagueness number example_instruction
crisp number Choose the square with 6 dots
crisp word Choose the square with the fewest dots
vague number Choose a square with about 10 dots
vague word Choose a square with few dots
These are the items:
Item Numbers.of.dots
1 06:15:24
2 16:25:34
3 26:35:44
4 36:45:54

Pre-process the raw data.

raw_data <- read.delim('e2-data.txt')
ggplot(data=raw_data, aes(RT_log)) + geom_density() +xlim(6,11)+ylim(0,0.8)
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density).

trim_data <- perSubjectTrim.fnc(data = raw_data[complete.cases(raw_data),], response='RT', subject='Subject', trim = 2.5)$data
## ......
